{
  "info": {
    "name": "Finance Dashboard API",
    "description": "Role-based finance management system built with FastAPI + SQLite.\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Run the backend: `uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000`\n2. Seed demo data: `python -m app.seed`\n3. Use **POST /auth/login** with one of the demo credentials to get a token\n4. The collection auto-saves the token — all subsequent requests are authenticated\n\n## Demo Credentials\n| Email | Password | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| admin@finance.dev | admin123 | Admin — full access |\n| analyst@finance.dev | analyst123 | Analyst — read + create/edit own |\n| viewer@finance.dev | viewer123 | Viewer — read only |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "finance-dashboard-api-v1"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Change to your deployed URL if hosted"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated after login"
    },
    {
      "key": "transactionId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated after creating a transaction"
    },
    {
      "key": "userId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated after creating a user"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Authentication endpoints — login, register, and current user profile.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login as Admin",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.access_token);",
                  "  console.log('Token saved. Role:', json.user.role);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Has access_token', () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access_token'));",
                  "pm.test('Role is admin', () => pm.expect(json.user.role).to.eql('admin'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@finance.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"admin123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login with admin credentials. The test script auto-saves the JWT token to the `{{token}}` collection variable — all subsequent requests use it automatically."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login as Analyst",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
